rtainment.ph/take-point-in-cinemas-march-20/|title=\"Take Point\" in cinemas March 20! {{!}} VIVA Entertainment Philippines - VIVA Entertainment Philippines|last=Furigay|first=Charlotte|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-04}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Hellboy (2019 film)|Hellboy]]''\n|April 10, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Lionsgate]], [[Millennium Films]], [[Campbell Grobman Films]], [[Dark Horse Entertainment]], Applebox Entertainment\n|\n|-\n|''[[Dragged Across Concrete]]''\n|July 17, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by Unified Pictures, Assemble Media, [[Cinestate]], Look to the Sky Films, Moot Point Productions\n|\n|-\n|''Isabelle''\n|July 24, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by Lazarus Effects, Out of the Blue... Entertainment, Rob Heydon Productions, The Wanting Film\n|\n|-\n|''Come on Irene''\n|July 31, 2019\n|{{flagicon|Japan}}\n|distribution only; produced by Star Sands, The Asahi Shimbun Company, VAP\n|\n|-\n|''[[Parasite (2019 film)|Parasite]]''\n|August 14, 2019\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}}\n|distribution only; produced by Barunson E&A Corp\n|\n|-\n|''[[Angel Has Fallen]]''\n|August 21, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Nu Image|Millennium Media]], G\u2013BASE\n|\n|-\n|''[[Polaroid (film)|Polaroid]]''\n|September 4, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Dimension Films]], Benderspink, Eldorado Film, [[Vertigo Entertainment]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[Rambo: Last Blood]]''\n|September 20, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Nu Image|Millennium Media]], [[Balboa Productions]], Templeton Media\n|\n|-\n|''Athlete''\n|September 25, 2019\n|{{flagicon|Japan}}\n|distribution only\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Wedding Year]]''\n|October 9, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Lakeshore Entertainment]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Current War]]''\n|October 16, 2019\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Bazelevs Company]], Film Rites, [[Thunder Road Pictures]]\n|\n|-\n|''Sadako''\n|October 30, 2019\n|{{flagicon|Japan}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Kadokawa Pictures]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Dude in Me]]''\n|November 6, 2019\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}}\n|distribution only; produced by The Contents On and [[Huayi Brothers Korea|Merry Christmas]]\n|\n|-\n|''Cinta itu Buta (Love is Blind)''\n|November 13, 2019\n|{{flagicon|Indonesia}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[mm2 Entertainment]], Reflection Pictures, and Timeless Pictures\n|\n|-\n|''[[More than Blue (2018 film)|More than Blue]]''\n|November 27, 2019\n|{{flagicon|Taiwan}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[mm2 Entertainment]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[Extreme Job]]''\n|December 11, 2019\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}}\n|distribution only; produced by About Film and Haegrim Pictures\n|\n|-\n|''Kill Chain''\n|January 15, 2020\n|{{flagicon|United States}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[CineTel Films]], ETA Films, Killing Link Productions, Millennium Media, Old City SAS, [[Saturn Films]]\n|\n|-\n|''Mia''\n|January 15, 2020\n|{{flagicon|Phiippines}}\n|distribution only; produced by Insight 360\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Informer (2019 film)|The Informer]]''\n|January 29, 2020\n|{{flagicon|United Kingdom}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Thunder Road Films|Thunder Road Pictures]] and The Fyzz Facility\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Room (2019 film)|The Room]]''\n|February 5, 2020\n|{{flagicon|France}}\n|distribution only; produced by Bidibul Productions, [[Les Films du Poisson]], and Versus Production\n|\n|-\n|''Kim Ji-Young, Born 1982''\n|February 12, 2020\n|{{flagicon|South Korea}}\n|distribution only; produced by [[Lotte Cultureworks]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Upcoming films==\n<!----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nAlthough the \"upcoming\" films are still in-progress (subject to change), please do make sure that you still add a RELIABLE reference/source for ANY information that you will add. Reliable references do NOT include blogs, unofficial facebook/twitter of key people, fansites, etc. ALL information with no source will be deleted. Thanks! :)\n\n\u2022 DO NOT RE-EDIT and remove the references/sources and additional information. All information added without references WILL BE DELETED.\n\n\u2022 ADDING REFERENCES \u2013 references should be placed in the notes section if the titled film has a wikipedia article. If the film does not have any link or article page here in Wikipedia, the reference should be indicated in the title of the film section.\n\n\u2022 If adding a film to the roster of upcoming films, PLEASE PLACE IT ACCORDING TO RELEASE DATE, WITH RELIABLE SOURCE/S. Thanks! :)\n\n!!!OTHER IMPORTANT NOTES BEFORE ADDING UPCOMING FILMS IN THE LIST:!!!\n\n1. UNTITLED FILM \u2013 If the film that you are going to place is still untitled but the news/article says the film is in either approved, legit, and is in production, please indicate it as \"Untitled film\".\n\n2. RELEASE DATE OF THE FILM \u2013 only put the release date of the film if it is officially announced by the production company or the news/article you have been put as sourced. If the film release date has not been announced, indicate or put it as \"TBA\" shortened for \"To be announced\".\n\n\u2022 EVERYTHING YOU HAVE BEEN CONTRIBUTED HERE WILL REFLECT TO THE PERSON WHO SEARCHES, VIEWS, VISITS, AND CHECKS THE ARTICLES FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD. IT IS IMPORTANT THAT WE CONTRIBUTE RELIABLY SO THAT WE CAN PROMOTE OUR OWN ENTERTAINMENT INDUSTRY.\n\n\u2022 THIS NOTE IS APPLICABLE TO THE ARTICLES OF FILM PRODUCTION OF THE PHILIPPINES HERE IN WIKIPEDIA\u2013BOTH ENGLISH AND TAGALOG.\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->\n;Color key\n{{plainlist|\n* {{Color box|#FFFACD|border=darkgray}} \u2013 a foreign film distributed by Viva International Pictures\n* {{Color box|#FFFFFF|border=dark