{"title_page": "List of Negro league baseball teams", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis '''list of Negro league baseball teams''' is based in part on the list maintained by the [[Negro Leagues Baseball Museum]] of [[Kansas City, Missouri]], in using the term \"Negro leagues\" for varying levels of [[African American|black]] baseball during [[racial segregation]] in the [[United States]]. Many of these teams reorganized or relocated which necessitated changing of names and frequently its players, staff and owner.\n\nTeams in '''bold''' are considered to have been of major league caliber for at least one season of their existence. Other teams were either a semi-pro, barnstorming or traveling team; a minor league team; or a team that existed after the integration of Major League Baseball (1946) when the talent level declined dramatically.\n{{Horizontal TOC|nonum=y|limit=2}}\n\n==Alabama==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n|  '''[[Birmingham Black Barons]]''' || 1920 || 1961 || [[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1920\u201323, 26, 31\u201336)<br>[[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1924\u201325, 27\u201330)<br>[[Negro American League|NAL]] (1937\u201338, 40\u201361) ||\n*NSL was a minor league every season except 1932\n*Did not field a team for 1939\n|| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coe.ksu.edu/nlbemuseum/history/teams/birmingbbarons.html|title=Birmingham Black Barons|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-02-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Birmingham Giants]] || 1907 || 1909 || Independent (1907\u201309) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seamheads.com/NegroLgs/organization.php?franchID=BG|title=Birmingham Giants|publisher=Gary Ashwill|editor=Gary Ashwill|work=Negro leagues database (Seamheads.com)|accessdate=2013-02-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Mobile Black Bears]] ||  ||  ||  ||  || <ref name=\"nlbm teams\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nlbm.com/s/team.htm|title=Negro league teams|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-02-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Mobile Tigers]] ||  ||  ||  ||  || {{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|- \n| [[Montgomery Grey Sox|Montgomery Grey Sox (I)]] || 1920 || 1921 || [[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1920)<br>Independent (1921) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nlbpa.com/the-negro-league-teams/montgomery-grey-sox|title=Montgomery Grey Sox|publisher=Negro League Baseball Players Association|accessdate=2013-02-12}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Montgomery Grey Sox|Montgomery Grey Sox (II)]]''' || 1931 || 1932 || Independent (1931)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1932) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?city=Montgomery&state=AL&country=US&empty=0|title=Montgomery, Alabama Negro League City Encyclopedia|work=Baseball-Reference.com|accessdate=2013-02-12}}</ref>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Arkansas==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- \n| [[Little Rock Black Travelers]] ||  ||  ||  ||  || <ref name=\"nlbm teams\"/>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==California==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#