ml|title=Jacksonville Red Caps|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-02-16}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Ethiopian Clowns'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Indianapolis Clowns|Indianapolis Clowns]]''')</small> || {{circa|1930s}} || 1942 || Independent ({{circa|lk=no|1930s}}\u201342) ||\n*Based in '''Miami'''\n*Also known as '''Miami Giants''' {{circa|lk=no|1930s}}\n|| {{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Georgia==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- id=\"Atlanta Black Crackers (I)\" style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| <u>'''[[Atlanta Black Crackers]]''' (I) '''club'''</u>\n*'''Atlanta Black Crackers''' (I) (1919\u201338)\n*'''Indianapolis ABCs''' (IV) (1939)\n|| 1919 || 1939 || <small>Ind.(19,22\u201325,28,30\u201331,33\u201334,37)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL(I)]](20\u201321,26\u201327,29,32,35\u201336)<br>[[Negro American League|NAL]] (1938\u201339)</small>\n ||\n*NSL was a minor league every season except 1932\n*Disestablished May 1939\n|| <ref name=\"Atlanta Black Crackers\">{{cite web|url=http://www.coe.ksu.edu/nlbemuseum/history/teams/atlantabcrackers.html|title=Atlanta Black Crackers|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-02-17}}</ref><ref name=\"Indianapolis ABCs\"/>\n|- \n| [[Atlanta Black Crackers (1943\u20131949)|Atlanta Black Crackers]] (II) || 1943 || 1949 || Independent (1943\u201344)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1945\u20131951)|NSL (II)]] (1945\u201347)<br>[[Negro American Association|NAA]] (1948\u201349)\n ||  || <ref name=\"Atlanta Black Crackers\"/>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Illinois==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\