0\u201331)|NNL1]] (1921) ||  || {{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Cincinnati Tigers]]''' || 1934 || 1937 || Independent (1934\u201336)<br>[[Negro American League|NAL]] (1937) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nlbpa.com/the-negro-league-teams/cincinnati-tigers|title=Cincinnati Tigers|publisher=Negro League Baseball Players Association|accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n=== Cleveland ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Cleveland Bears'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Jacksonville Red Caps|Jacksonville Red Caps]]''')</small> || 1939 || 1940 || [[Negro American League|NAL]] (1939\u201340) ||  || <ref name=\"Jacksonville Red Caps\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Cleveland Browns (baseball)|Cleveland Browns]]''' || 1924 || 1924 || [[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1924) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seamheads.com/NegroLgs/organization.php?franchID=CBN|title=Cleveland Browns|publisher=Gary Ashwill|editor=Gary Ashwill|work=Negro leagues database (Seamheads.com)|accessdate=2013-09-21}}</ref>\n|- id=\"Cleveland Buckeyes\" style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| <u>'''[[Cleveland Buckeyes]] club'''</u>\n*'''Cincinnati-Cleveland Buckeyes''' (1942)\n*'''Cleveland Buckeyes''' (1943\u201348)\n*'''Louisville Buckeyes''' (1949)\n*'''Cleveland Buckeyes''' (1950)\n|| 1942 || 1950 || [[Negro American League|NAL]] (1942\u201350) ||\n*Half of 1942 home schedule in Cincinnati, half in Cleveland\n*Disbanded mid-season 1950\n|| <ref name=\"Cleveland Buckeyes\"/>\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?id=e9d57483|title=1942 Cincinnati/Cleveland Buckeyes|work=Baseball.Reference.com|accessdate=2014-05-29}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Cleveland Cubs'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Baltimore Elite Giants|Baltimore Elite Giants]]''')</small> || 1931 || 1931 || [[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1931) ||  || <ref name=\"Elite Giants\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Cleveland Elites]]''' (1926)<br>'''[[Cleveland Hornets]]''' (1927)<br>'''[[Cleveland Tigers (baseball)|Cleveland Tigers]]''' (1928) || 1926 || 1928 || [[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1926\u201328) ||\n*Teams are considered separate but closely linked\n|| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?id=3f0f26a9|title=1926 Cleveland Elites|work=Baseball-Reference.com|accessdate=2013-10-08}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?id=bfa2585d|title=1927 Cleveland Hornets|work=Baseball-Reference.com|accessdate=2013-10-08}}</ref><br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seamheads.com/NegroLgs/organization.php?franchID=CLT|title=Cleveland Tigers|publisher=Gary Ashwill|editor=Gary Ashwill|work=Negro leagues database (Seamheads.com)|accessdate=2013-10-08}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Cleveland Giants]]''' || 1933 || 1933 || [[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1933) ||\n*Formed from remnants of the '''Akron Black Tyrites''' for end of 1933\n|| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seamheads.com/NegroLgs/organization.php?franchID=CG|title=Cleveland Giants|publisher=Gary Ashwill|editor=Gary Ashwill|work=Negro leagues database (Seamheads.com)|accessdate=2013-09-20}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Cleveland Red Sox]]''' || 1934 || 1934 || [[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1934) ||\n*Only season in existence\n|| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?id=0a5b67f3|title=1934 Cleveland Red Sox|work=Baseball-Reference.com|accessdate=2013-10-08}}</re