and Giants|publisher=Negro League Baseball Players Association|accessdate=2013-03-29}}</ref>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Indiana==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Cole's American Giants'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Chicago American Giants|Chicago American Giants]]''')</small> || 1933 || 1933 || [[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1933) ||\n*Played majority of home games temporarily in '''Indianapolis''' 1933\n|| <ref name=\"Chicago American Giants\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Indianapolis ABCs]]''' (I) || {{circa|1913}} || 1926 || Independent (1913\u201319)<br>[[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1920\u201326) ||  || <ref name=\"Indianapolis ABCs\">{{cite web|url=http://coe.ksu.edu/nlbemuseum/history/teams/indyabcs.html|title=Indianapolis ABCs|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-03-22}}</ref>\n|- id=\"Indianapolis ABCs (II)\" style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| <u>'''[[Indianapolis ABCs]]''' (II) '''club'''</u>\n*'''Indianapolis ABCs''' (II) (1931\u201333)\n*'''Detroit Stars''' (II) (1933)\n|| 1931 || 1933 || [[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1931)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1932)<br>[[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1933) ||\n*Relocated to Detroit shortly after opening day 1933\n|| <ref name=\"Indianapolis ABCs\"/><ref name=\"Detroit Stars\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Indianapolis ABCs''' (III)<br><small>(See '''[[#St. Louis Stars (III)|St. Louis Stars (III)]]''')</small> || 1938 || 1938 || [[Negro American League|NAL]] (1938) ||  || <ref name=\"Indianapolis ABCs\"/><ref name=\"St. Louis S