lumbus Buckeyes (Negro leagues)|Columbus Buckeyes]]''' || 1921 || 1921 || [[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1921) ||\n*Only season in existence\n|| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seamheads.com/NegroLgs/organization.php?franchID=COB|title=Columbus Buckeyes|publisher=Gary Ashwill|editor=Gary Ashwill|work=Negro leagues database (Seamheads.com)|accessdate=2013-09-20}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Columbus Elite Giants'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Baltimore Elite Giants|Baltimore Elite Giants]]''')</small> || 1935 || 1935 || [[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1935) ||  || <ref name=\"Elite Giants\"/>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Columbus Turfs'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Louisville Black Caps|Louisville Black Caps]]''')</small> || 1932 || 1932 || [[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1932) ||\n*Relocated from Louisville in August then folded at end of season\n|| <ref name=\"nlbm teams\"/>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Oregon==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- \n| [[Portland Rosebuds (baseball)|Portland Rosebuds]] || 1946 || 1946 || [[West Coast Negro Baseball League|WCNBL]] (1946) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?id=d86e7a36|title=1946 Portland Rosebuds|work=Baseball-Reference.com|accessdate=2013-10-08}}</ref>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Pennsylvania==\n\n=== Harrisburg ===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; 