all History, 1920-1951, By William J. Plott (2015) p, 9. McFarland & Company. ISBN 978-0-7864-7544-5</ref>\n\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''[[Memphis Red Sox]]'''|| 1923 || 1962 || Independent (1923)<br>[[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1924\u201325, 27\u201330)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1926, 31\u201336)<br>[[Negro American League|NAL]] (1937\u201362) ||  || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://coe.ksu.edu/nlbemuseum/history/teams/memphisrsox.html|title=Memphis Red Sox|publisher=Negro Leagues Baseball Museum|accessdate=2013-03-27}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background:#ffffe0;\" \n| '''Nashville Elite Giants'''<br><small>(See '''[[#Baltimore Elite Giants|Baltimore Elite Giants]]''')</small> || 1919 || 1934 || Independent (1919\u201329)<br>[[Negro National League (1920\u201331)|NNL1]] (1930)<br>[[Negro Southern League (1920\u201336)|NSL]] (1932)<br>[[Negro National League (1933\u201348)|NNL2]] (1933\u201334) ||\n*Known as '''Nashville Standard Giants''' 1919\u201320\n*Relocated as '''Cleveland Cubs''' 1931 then returned to Nashville\n|| <ref name=\"Elite Giants\"/>\n|}\n{{Top of page}}\n\n==Texas==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#a8bdec; width:26%;\"| Team !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| 1st Yr !! style=\"width:7%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Last Yr !! style=\"width:16%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Affiliation(s) !! style=\"width:40%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Notes !! style=\"width:4%; background:#a8bdec;\"| Ref\n|- \n| [[Austin Black Senators]] ||  ||  ||  ||  || {{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|- \n| [[Brenham Merchants]] ||  ||  ||  ||  || {{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n|- \n| Houston Eagles<br><small>(See '''[[#Newark Eagles|Newark Eagles]]''')</small> || 1949 || 1950 || [[Negro American League|NAL]] (1949\u201350) ||\n*Folded after 1950 season\n|| <ref name=\"Newark Eagles\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.baseball-reference.com/nlb/team.cgi?city=Houston&state=TX&country=US&empty=0|ti